headline: How Investors Are Reacting To Tutor Perini (TPC) Winning A Specialized Defense Facility Contract
summary: Tutor Perini Management Services recently secured a US$35.8 million contract to build a 56,000-square-foot tool and die facility at the Iowa Army Ammunition Plant in Middletown, Iowa, with work already underway and substantial completion targeted for June 2027. The project’s broad scope, from site development and utilities to solar power and overhead bridge cranes, underscores Tutor Perini’s capabilities in complex, federally funded defense infrastructure work. headline: The Publicity War Between AT&T and T-Mobile Is Getting Ugly
summary: AT&T, T-Mobile US and Verizon are escalating their usual claims about whose wireless service is best with the launch of explicit customer poaching efforts and litigation.
